Methods

addObserver

  • addObserver(observer: Observer): void
    • Defined in davinci-newton/util/Subject.ts:32

    Adds the given Observer to the Subject's list of Observers, so that the Observer will be notified of changes in this Subject. Does nothing if the Observer is already on the list. An Observer may call Subject.addObserver during its observe method.

    Parameters

    • observer: Observer

      the Observer to add to list of Observers

    Returns void

broadcast

  • broadcast(event: SubjectEvent): void
    • Defined in davinci-newton/util/Subject.ts:39

    Notifies all Observers that the Subject has changed by calling observe on each Observer. An Observer may call Subject.addObserver or Subject.removeObserver during its observe method.

    Parameters

    • event: SubjectEvent

      a SubjectEvent with information relating to the change.

    Returns void

broadcastParameter

  • broadcastParameter(name: string): void
    • Defined in davinci-newton/util/Subject.ts:47

    Notifies all Observers that the Parameter with the given name has changed by calling {@link myphysicslab.lab.util.Observer#observe} on each Observer.

    throws

    if there is no Parameter with the given name

    Parameters

    • name: string

      the universal or English name of the Parameter that has changed

    Returns void
